<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4472154>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 90. Rear left leg tibia showing (left photo) 3 outer spines (with a bump [arrow] indicating a small 4th spine), and (right photo) with 4 inner spines. Note the presence of only 4 articulated calcars in the ringlet of 6, indicating possible injury during an earlier instar. Unfortunately, the holotype lacks his right rear leg making comparison impossible." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4472154/files/figure.png" .

